quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  12,70,"Then, when he had supplied them with their supplies, he placed the drinking-cup in his brother’s saddlebag. Then an announcer called out, “O caravan{1}, most surely you are thieves.”",footnotes:1:A metaphor for the people of the caravan.
  12,71,"They said as they came towards them, “What are you missing?”"
  12,72,"They said, “We are missing the king’s goblet. And whoever comes up with it will have a camel-load, and I{1}guarantee it.”",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from plural to singular.
  12,73,"They said, “<i class=""s"">(We swear) </i>by Allah, you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>have most surely known that we did not come to spread corruption in the land, and never have we been thieves.”"
  12,74,"They said, “What shall be his repayment, if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>are lying?”"
  12,75,"They said, “The repayment should be that he in whose saddlebag it is found, he himself is the repayment{1}. Thus we repay the unjust ones.”",footnotes:1:That he becomes enslaved.
  12,76,"So he began with their bags before his brother’s bag, then he extracted it from his brother’s bag. Thus We plotted for Joseph; he could not have seized his brother according to the king’s religion{1}unless Allah wills. <span class=""h"">We elevate by degrees<sup foot_note=""80307"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>whomever We so will. For above everyone who has knowledge, there is One who is All-Knowing.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is deenwhich means ‘a way of life’, ‘religion’ or ‘recompense’.
  12,77,"They said, “If he steals, well, actually a brother of his has stolen before.” But Joseph kept it secret within himself and did not reveal it to them. He said<i class=""s"">(to himself) </i>, “You<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>are in a worse situation, and Allah knows better of what you describe.”"
  12,78,"They said, “O mighty governor, he has a father<i class=""s"">(who is) </i>a very old man, so take one of us in his place; we see that you are of those who excel in doing good.”"
